ults are not output separately but are stored in the final.out file. The results of read alignment can be verified using the Log.final.out file, which provides information about the total unique reads, multi-mapping reads, and unmapped reads. Due to the large size of the STAR-generated .sam files, they are converted into smaller-sized binary format .bam files.","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"key":"CCvxAfMjT1"},{"type":"break","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"key":"Cj1Bz8U7L3"},{"type":"text","value":"To align the mapping information after read mapping, the samtools’ ","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"key":"Mb1bi0NI22"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"view","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"key":"XOmZ24ZOd0"},{"type":"text","value":" and ","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"key":"lT8syhc6kB"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"sort","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"key":"yORkydtHTG"},{"type":"text","value":" functions are utilized to transform the .sam files into .bam files.","position":{"start":{"line":26,"column":1},"end":{"line":26,"column":1}},"key":"d0Ln2NjleZ"}],"key":"MukAjr4L3M"},{"type":"code","lang":"bash","value":"#install samtools\n$ tar -xvf samtools.zip\n$ cd samtools\n$ ./configure -prefix==/where/to/install\n$ make\n$ make install\n#sam file sorting and indexing\n$ samtools view -b -F 4 sample_Aligned.out.sam | samtools sort - > sample.bam\n$ samtools index sample.bam","position":{"start":{"line":30,"column":1},"end":{"line":40,"column":1}},"key":"SsWiLufvrY"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":42,"column":1},"end":{"line":44,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Once these .bam files are generated, you can visualize the alignment results using the IGV program. To examine the alignment results with the IGV program, you will need the MAG.fa obtained from metagenome de novo assembly or MAG results. If you wish to display annotated coding sequences (CDS) information within the MAG.fa sequences, you can import an annotation-generated .gff file* as well.\nAdditionally, you will require the .bam files containing coverage value information resulting from the application of samtools and the .bam.bai file generated by ","position":{"start":{"line":42,"column":1},"end":{"line":42,"column":1}},"key":"taBkxn3hkj"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"samtools index","position":{"start":{"line":42,"column":1},"end":{"line":42,"column":1}},"key":"iCwl1ctDmq"},{"type":"text","value":". Once all these files are imported, the visualization will display information on CDS in the reference sequence, the location of mapping of metatranscriptomic sequence reads, and the count of metatranscriptomic reads mapped at each position.","position":{"start":{"line":42,"column":1},"end":{"line":42,"column":1}},"key":"JSm6ZGm6yh"},{"type":"break","position":{"start":{"line":42,"column":1},"end":{"line":42,"column":1}},"key":"OcNXLpKXIP"},{"type":"text","value":"*Note: The creation of a .gff (General Feature Format) file for MAG.fa can be referred to in the metagenome SOP.","position":{"start":{"line":42,"column":1},"end":{"line":42,"column":1}},"key":"yNFNoWOFao"}],"key":"nwTlXgroGJ"},{"type":"container","children":[{"type":"image","style":{"width":"90%"},"url":"/metainsight-book/build/8512a1191694788420b9e84605b5e5e7.png","alt":"Visualization of alignment result using IGV program","data":{"altTextIsAutoGenerated":true},"key":"Iy5c1OHkgt","urlSource":"https://github.com/sujin9819/MetaInsight/blob/main/SOP/MetaTranscriptomic/img/T_6_3.png?raw=true"},{"type":"caption","children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Visualization of alignment result using IGV program","key":"JmNwuNGMqh"}],"key":"Q7VcTkWOyF"}],"key":"jFubKY58SI"}],"key":"HiZtRMFKKe"